{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775855948354,"sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","part":{"id":"prt_d79434e15001B0m5JIlDZjrfZr","messageID":"msg_d794342ac001Ldk8hG1Y597lf8","sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_835564d1ca844f6fa0ce895d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec covers the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands, their runtime classes (`InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`), and associated provider integrations (`AgentCubeProvider`, `KubernetesProvider`).\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## invoke Command\n17: \n18: ### Requirement: invoke command entry point\n19: \n20: The system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that POSTs JSON payload to the published agent endpoint, supporting both `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service) providers.\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: invoke options and defaults\n23: \n24: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n25: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be:\n26:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\n27:   - `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`)\n28:   - `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`)\n29:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`, `str`)\n30:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: payload JSON parsing\n33: \n34: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--payload '{\"input\": \"hello\"}'`\n35: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n36: - **THEN** the system SHALL deserialize it to `{\"input\": \"hello\"}` and pass it to `InvokeRuntime.invoke`\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: invalid payload JSON\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** `--payload` is not valid JSON (e.g., `--payload '{bad}'`)\n41: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n42: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error: Invalid JSON payload: {detail}` in red and exit with code `1` (before calling `_handle_error`)\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: header parsing\n45: \n46: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token123\"`\n47: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n48: - **THEN** the system SHALL split on the first `:` to produce `{\"Authorization\": \"Bearer token123\"}` (stripped key/value)\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: invalid header format\n51: \n52: - **GIVEN** a header string without a `:` separator (e.g., `--header \"BadHeader\"`)\n53: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n54: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error: Invalid header format. Expected 'key:value'.` in red and exit with code `1`\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: multiple headers\n57: \n58: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\" --header \"X-Custom: value\"`\n59: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n60: - **THEN** the system SHALL merge all into a single `Dict[str, str]`\n61: \n62: #### Scenario: session header injection\n63: \n64: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n65: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n66: - **THEN** the HTTP request SHALL include header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` with the session value\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: AgentCube provider URL rewriting\n69: \n70: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n71: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube` runs\n72: - **THEN** the endpoint URL SHALL be rewritten to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n73: \n74: #### Scenario: invoke prerequisites validation\n75: \n76: - **GIVEN** the workspace lacks published metadata (no `agent_id` or `agent_endpoint`)\n77: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites` runs\n78: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the agent must be published first\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: successful invoke response\n81: \n82: - **GIVEN** a valid endpoint and payload\n83: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation` completes\n84: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the response (Rich-formatted if JSON, raw text otherwise)\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: invoke HTTP error\n87: \n88: - **GIVEN** the endpoint returns a non-2xx status\n89: - **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` receives the response\n90: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise an exception surfaced via `_handle_error` with the status code and response body\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: invoke error handling\n93: \n94: - **GIVEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` raises\n95: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n96: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error invoking agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## status Command\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: status command entry point\n103: \n104: The system SHALL provide a `status` subcommand that loads workspace metadata and displays agent status in a Rich `Table`.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: status options and defaults\n107: \n108: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n109: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be:\n110:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`)\n111:   - `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`, `str`)\n112:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\n113: \n114: #### Scenario: not published status\n115: \n116: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n117: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n118: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to run `publish` first and exit with code `1`\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR status\n121: \n122: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube` and the CR exists in K8s\n123: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n124: - **THEN** status SHALL be read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` when present (fields: `status`, `agentEndpoint`), else `created_no_status`, else `not_found_in_k8s`\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: standard K8s status\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s`\n129: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status` runs\n130: - **THEN** the system SHALL query `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` and return deployment/pod status\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: status display\n133: \n134: - **GIVEN** status data is available\n135: - **WHEN** the status command completes\n136: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL render a Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value (including at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider)\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: status error\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` returns `status == \"error\"`\n141: - **WHEN** the status command processes the result\n142: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the error details and exit with code `1`\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: status error handling\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` raises\n147: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n148: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error getting status: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## InvokeRuntime\n153: \n154: ### Requirement: InvokeRuntime class\n155: \n156: The system SHALL implement `InvokeRuntime` with provider-aware invocation logic.\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: constructor\n159: \n160: - **GIVEN** `InvokeRuntime(verbose=False, provider=\"agentcube\")` is instantiated\n161: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n162: - **THEN** `self.verbose` and `self.provider` SHALL be set accordingly\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: invoke method\n165: \n166: - **GIVEN** a valid `workspace_path`, `payload` (Dict), and optional `headers` (Dict[str, str])\n167: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` is called\n168: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n169:   1. Call `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)` to get metadata, agent_id, and endpoint\n170:   2. If `provider == \"agentcube\"`, call `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube`\n171:   3. Otherwise, call `_direct_http_invocation`\n172:   4. Return the response\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: _validate_invoke_prerequisites\n175: \n176: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace with published metadata\n177: - **WHEN** `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` runs\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL return `(metadata, agent_id, endpoint)` tuple\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: _invoke_agent_via_agentcube\n181: \n182: - **GIVEN** an agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, and workspace_path\n183: - **WHEN** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` runs\n184: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n185:   1. Rewrite endpoint if `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`\n186:   2. Add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header if `metadata.session_id` exists\n187:   3. POST JSON to the endpoint\n188:   4. Return the parsed response\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: _direct_http_invocation\n191: \n192: - **GIVEN** an endpoint, payload, headers, and workspace_path\n193: - **WHEN** `_direct_http_invocation` runs\n194: - **THEN** it SHALL POST JSON to `{endpoint}` and return the response dict\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## StatusRuntime\n199: \n200: ### Requirement: StatusRuntime class\n201: \n202: The system SHALL implement `StatusRuntime` with provider-aware status retrieval.\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: constructor\n205: \n206: - **GIVEN** `StatusRuntime(verbose=False, provider=\"agentcube\")` is instantiated\n207: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n208: - **THEN** `self.verbose` and `self.provider` SHALL be set accordingly\n209: \n210: #### Scenario: get_status method\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** a `workspace_path` and optional `provider`\n213: - **WHEN** `StatusRuntime.get_status` is called\n214: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n215:   1. Load metadata from workspace\n216:   2. If no `agent_id`, return `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}`\n217:   3. If `provider == \"agentcube\"`, call `_get_cr_k8s_status`\n218:   4. Otherwise, call `_get_k8s_status`\n219:   5. Return the status dict\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: _get_cr_k8s_status with existing CR\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists and has a `status` field\n224: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n225: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": cr_status, \"endpoint\": cr_agentEndpoint, ...}`\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: _get_cr_k8s_status with CR but no status\n228: \n229: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no `status` field\n230: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n231: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}`\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: _get_cr_k8s_status with missing CR\n234: \n235: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CR does not exist\n236: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n237: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}`\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: _get_k8s_status\n240: \n241: - **GIVEN** a standard K8s deployment\n242: - **WHEN** `_get_k8s_status` runs\n243: - **THEN** it SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` and return the result\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## Cross-cutting\n248: \n249: ### Requirement: Error handling for invoke/status\n250: \n251: Both commands SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions.\n252: \n253: #### Scenario: verbose traceback\n254: \n255: - **GIVEN** a subcommand's local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n256: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n257: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand's `verbose` flag\n258: \n259: ### Requirement: Provider selection\n260: \n261: The `--provider` flag SHALL determine which backend is used for both invoke and status.\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: provider=agentcube\n264: \n265: - **GIVEN** `--provider agentcube`\n266: - **WHEN** invoke or status runs\n267: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `AgentCubeProvider` for K8s CR operations\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: provider=k8s\n270: \n271: - **GIVEN** `--provider k8s`\n272: - **WHEN** invoke or status runs\n273: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `KubernetesProvider` for standard K8s operations\n\n(End of file - total 273 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/spec.md`, `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec covers the `invoke` and `status` CLI commands, their runtime classes (`InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`), and associated provider integrations (`AgentCubeProvider`, `KubernetesProvider`).\n\n---\n\n## invoke Command\n\n### Requirement: invoke command entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `invoke` subcommand that POSTs JSON payload to the published agent endpoint, supporting both `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment/Service) providers.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775855948344,"end":1775855948352}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775855949558,"sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","part":{"id":"prt_d794352c9001BwPDj1rmNyBwrQ","messageID":"msg_d794342ac001Ldk8hG1Y597lf8","sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bc924614ebc44b34aee096ee","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: 为 AgentCube Python CLI（`kubectl-agentcube`）实现 `invoke` 和 `status` 两个子命令，补全 Agent 从打包、构建、发布到调用和状态查询的完整生命周期。\n6: \n7: 当前 CLI 已实现 `pack`、`build`、`publish` 命令，但用户部署 Agent 后无法通过 CLI 验证其是否正常工作或查看运行状态。本 AR 补齐最后两个关键操作。\n8: \n9: ## Scope\n10: \n11: ### In Scope\n12: \n13: 1. **`invoke` 命令**\n14:    - 向已部署的 Agent 发送 HTTP POST 请求\n15:    - 支持 `--payload` 传递 JSON 输入（默认 `\"{}\"`）\n16:    - 支持 `--header` 添加自定义 HTTP Header（可重复指定）\n17:    - 支持 `--provider` 选择 `agentcube`（AgentRuntime CR）或 `k8s`（标准 Deployment/Service）\n18:    - AgentCube Provider 自动将 endpoint 重写为 `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n19:    - 若元数据包含 `session_id`，自动添加 `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` Header\n20:    - 打印响应结果，异常通过 `_handle_error` 处理\n21: \n22: 2. **`status` 命令**\n23:    - 加载 workspace 元数据（`agent_metadata.yaml`）\n24:    - 根据 `--provider` 查询对应资源状态\n25:    - AgentCube Provider：通过 `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime` 查询 CR 状态\n26:    - K8s Provider：通过 `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` 查询 Deployment/Service 状态\n27:    - 使用 Rich Table 渲染状态信息\n28:    - `not_published` 或 `error` 状态时打印提示并 `typer.Exit(1)`\n29: \n30: 3. **错误处理**\n31:    - `invoke`：JSON payload 解析失败、Header 格式错误直接退出码 1\n32:    - 运行时异常统一走 `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`\n33: \n34: ### Out of Scope\n35: \n36: - 修复 `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube` 的已知 UnboundLocalError（条件分支未覆盖非 http 开头的 endpoint）\n37: - 新增 Provider 类型\n38: - SDK 层改动\n39: - Python CLI 以外的组件（Go CLI、Controller 等）\n40: \n41: ## Impact Analysis\n42: \n43: ### Dependencies\n44: \n45: | 依赖 | 用途 | 影响 |\n46: |------|------|------|\n47: | `InvokeRuntime`（已有） | invoke 核心逻辑 | 无影响，CLI 仅调用 |\n48: | `StatusRuntime`（已有） | status 核心逻辑 | 无影响，CLI 仅调用 |\n49: | `AgentCubeProvider`（已有） | CR 查询 | 无影响 |\n50: | `KubernetesProvider`（已有） | 标准 K8s 查询 | 无影响 |\n51: | `_handle_error`（已有） | 错误处理 | 无影响 |\n52: | `typer`、`rich`（已有） | CLI 框架和渲染 | 无影响 |\n53: \n54: ### Affected Components\n55: \n56: - **`agentcube/cli/main.py`**（修改）：新增 `invoke` 和 `status` 两个 `@app.command()` 函数\n57: - **无新增文件**：完全复用现有 Runtime 类和 Provider\n58: \n59: ### 与现有组件的交互\n60: \n61: | 组件 | 交互方式 | 影响 |\n62: |------|----------|------|\n63: | `InvokeRuntime` | CLI 实例化并调用 `invoke()` | 无影响 |\n64: | `StatusRuntime` | CLI 实例化并调用 `get_status()` | 无影响 |\n65: | `MetadataService` | Runtime 内部加载元数据 | 无影响 |\n66: | `AgentCubeProvider` | StatusRuntime 内部查询 CR | 无影响 |\n67: | `KubernetesProvider` | StatusRuntime 内部查询 Deployment | 无影响 |\n68: \n69: ### Risk Assessment\n70: \n71: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n72: |------|------|----------|\n73: | `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` UnboundLocalError | 中 | CLI 层通过 `_handle_error` 捕获，用户看到友好错误信息 |\n74: | K8s 客户端初始化失败（kubeconfig 不存在等） | 低 | Runtime 层已有异常处理，CLI 层透传 |\n75: | Header 解析歧义（value 含 `:`） | 低 | 使用 `split(\":\", 1)` 仅分割第一个冒号 |\n76: | 元数据缺失必要字段 | 低 | Runtime 层 `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` 已处理 |\n77: \n78: ## Alternatives Considered\n79: \n80: ### 1. CLI 层直接调用 Provider（❌ 不采用）\n81: \n82: **做法**：CLI 命令直接实例化 `AgentCubeProvider` / `KubernetesProvider`，跳过 Runtime 层。\n83: \n84: **优点**：减少一层封装  \n85: **缺点**：\n86: - 违反现有架构（pack/build/publish 均通过 Runtime 层）\n87: - 需重复实现元数据加载、验证逻辑\n88: - 破坏关注点分离\n89: \n90: **决策**：不采用。保持与现有命令一致的架构模式。\n91: \n92: ### 2. 合并 invoke 和 status 为单一命令（❌ 不采用）\n93: \n94: **做法**：`kubectl-agentcube agent <name> [--action invoke|status]`\n95: \n96: **优点**：减少子命令数量  \n97: **缺点**：\n98: - 与现有 `pack`/`build`/`publish` 的扁平子命令风格不一致\n99: - 参数差异大（invoke 需要 payload/header，status 不需要）\n100: - 违反 CLI 设计最佳实践（一个命令一个职责）\n101: \n102: **决策**：不采用。保持独立的 `invoke` 和 `status` 子命令。\n103: \n104: ### 3. 通过 Runtime 层调用（✅ 选定方案）\n105: \n106: **做法**：CLI 实例化 `InvokeRuntime` / `StatusRuntime`，调用其公开方法。\n107: \n108: **优点**：\n109: - 与现有 `pack`/`build`/`publish` 架构完全一致\n110: - Runtime 层已封装元数据加载、Provider 选择、错误处理\n111: - CLI 层职责单一：参数解析 → Runtime 调用 → 结果展示\n112: \n113: **缺点**：\n114: - 依赖 Runtime 层的实现质量（已知 UnboundLocalError）\n115: \n116: **决策**：采用。Runtime 层已知问题不影响 CLI 层正确性，错误会被 `_handle_error` 捕获。\n117: \n118: ## Implementation Notes\n119: \n120: ### invoke 命令实现\n121: \n122: ```python\n123: @app.command()\n124: def invoke(\n125:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n126:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\"),\n127:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n128:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n129:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n130: ) -> None:\n131:     \"\"\"Invoke a deployed agent with a JSON payload.\"\"\"\n132:     try:\n133:         payload_dict = json.loads(payload)\n134:     except json.JSONDecodeError:\n135:         typer.echo(f\"Error: Invalid JSON payload: {payload}\", err=True)\n136:         raise typer.Exit(1)\n137: \n138:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\n139:     if header_list:\n140:         headers = {}\n141:         for h in header_list:\n142:             if \":\" not in h:\n143:                 typer.echo(f\"Error: Invalid header format '{h}'. Expected 'key:value'.\", err=True)\n144:                 raise typer.Exit(1)\n145:             key, value = h.split(\":\", 1)\n146:             headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n147: \n148:     try:\n149:         runtime = InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n150:         result = runtime.invoke(Path(workspace), payload_dict, headers)\n151:         typer.echo(json.dumps(result, indent=2) if isinstance(result, dict) else result)\n152:     except Exception as e:\n153:         _handle_error(e, \"invoke\", verbose)\n154: ```\n155: \n156: ### status 命令实现\n157: \n158: ```python\n159: @app.command()\n160: def status(\n161:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\", show_default=True),\n162:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\"),\n163:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging\"),\n164: ) -> None:\n165:     \"\"\"Check the status of a deployed agent.\"\"\"\n166:     try:\n167:         runtime = StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n168:         status_result = runtime.get_status(Path(workspace), provider)\n169: \n170:         if status_result.get(\"status\") == \"not_published\":\n171:             typer.echo(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\", err=True)\n172:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n173: \n174:         if status_result.get(\"status\") == \"error\":\n175:             typer.echo(f\"Error retrieving status: {status_result.get('message', 'Unknown error')}\", err=True)\n176:             raise typer.Exit(1)\n177: \n178:         table = Table(title=\"Agent Status\")\n179:         table.add_column(\"Field\", style=\"cyan\")\n180:         table.add_column(\"Value\", style=\"green\")\n181:         for key, value in status_result.items():\n182:             table.add_row(key, str(value))\n183:         console = Console()\n184:         console.print(table)\n185:     except typer.Exit:\n186:         raise\n187:     except Exception as e:\n188:         _handle_error(e, \"status\", verbose)\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### 测试策略\n192: \n193: - **单元测试**：mock `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` 和 `StatusRuntime.get_status()`，验证 CLI 层参数传递、错误处理、退出码\n194: - **边界用例**：\n195:   - 无效 JSON payload → 退出码 1\n196:   - 无效 Header 格式 → 退出码 1\n197:   - `not_published` 状态 → 退出码 1 + 提示信息\n198:   - `error` 状态 → 退出码 1 + 错误信息\n199: - **集成测试**：使用真实 workspace + 元数据文件验证完整链路（可选，依赖 K8s 集群）\n200: \n201: ## Acceptance Criteria\n202: \n203: 1. **invoke 命令**\n204:    - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` 显示正确参数说明\n205:    - [ ] 默认 payload `\"{}\"` 可正常发送\n206:    - [ ] `--payload '{\"key\": \"value\"}'` 正确解析并发送\n207:    - [ ] `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"` 正确添加到请求\n208:    - [ ] `--header` 可重复指定多个 Header\n209:    - [ ] 无效 JSON payload 打印错误并退出码 1\n210:    - [ ] 无效 Header 格式打印错误并退出码 1\n211:    - [ ] AgentCube Provider 路径重写生效\n212:    - [ ] `session_id` 存在时自动添加 `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` Header\n213:    - [ ] 运行时异常走 `_handle_error`\n214: \n215: 2. **status 命令**\n216:    - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube status --help` 显示正确参数说明\n217:    - [ ] AgentCube Provider 查询 CR 状态并展示 Rich Table\n218:    - [ ] K8s Provider 查询 Deployment 状态并展示 Rich Table\n219:    - [ ] `not_published` 状态打印提示并退出码 1\n220:    - [ ] `error` 状态打印错误并退出码 1\n221:    - [ ] 运行时异常走 `_handle_error`\n222: \n223: 3. **代码质量**\n224:    - [ ] 与现有 `pack`/`build`/`publish` 命令风格一致\n225:    - [ ] 无新增依赖\n226:    - [ ] 通过现有 lint/typecheck\n227: \n228: ## Status\n229: \n230: - [ ] 提案审查\n231: - [ ] 实现\n232: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 232 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023: CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube Python CLI（`kubectl-agentcube`）实现 `invoke` 和 `status` 两个子命令，补全 Agent 从打包、构建、发布到调用和状态查询的完整生命周期。\n\n当前 CLI 已实现 `pack`、`build`、`publish` 命令，但用户部署 Agent 后无法通过 CLI 验证其是否正常工作或查看运行状态。本 AR 补齐最后两个关键操作。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **`invoke` 命令**\n   - 向已部署的 Agent 发送 HTTP POST 请求\n   - 支持 `--payload` 传递 JSON 输入（默认 `\"{}\"`）\n   - 支持 `--header` 添加自定义 HTTP Header（可重复指定）\n   - 支持 `--provider` 选择 `agentcube`（AgentRuntime CR）或 `k8s`（标准 Deployment/Service）\n   - AgentCube Provider 自动将 endpoint 重写为 `/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n   - 若元数据包含 `session_id`，自动添加 `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` Header\n   - 打印响应结果，异常通过 `_handle_error` 处理","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775855949550,"end":1775855949557}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775855949648,"sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","part":{"id":"prt_d7943573a001J4egeN2GuAJThK","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d794342ac001Ldk8hG1Y597lf8","sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":47997,"input":47788,"output":139,"reasoning":70,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0.013534547}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775855951836,"sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","part":{"id":"prt_d79435fd9001n0u5IhaRior2YE","messageID":"msg_d79435768001UtT3BYtK9Wgt4o","sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775855954001,"sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","part":{"id":"prt_d794363c60011BtLdbfo8MlCEd","messageID":"msg_d79435768001UtT3BYtK9Wgt4o","sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_482ed9048f054482aee2b3f3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"AgentCube CLI entry point.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: import logging\n6: from typing import Optional\n7: \n8: import typer\n9: from rich.console import Console\n10: from rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n11: \n12: from pathlib import Path\n13: \n14: from agentcube import __version__\n15: from agentcube.runtime.pack_runtime import PackRuntime\n16: from agentcube.runtime.build_runtime import BuildRuntime\n17: from agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime import PublishRuntime\n18: \n19: app = typer.Typer(\n20:     name=\"agentcube\",\n21:     help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\",\n22:     no_args_is_help=True,\n23:     rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n24:     add_completion=False,\n25: )\n26: \n27: console = Console()\n28: \n29: \n30: def version_callback(value: Optional[bool]) -> None:\n31:     \"\"\"Print version and exit.\"\"\"\n32:     if value:\n33:         console.print(f\"agentcube {__version__}\")\n34:         raise typer.Exit()\n35: \n36: \n37: @app.callback()\n38: def main(\n39:     version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(\n40:         None,\n41:         \"--version\",\n42:         help=\"Show version and exit.\",\n43:         callback=version_callback,\n44:         is_eager=True,\n45:     ),\n46:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output.\"),\n47: ) -> None:\n48:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n49:     if verbose:\n50:         logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n51: \n52: \n53: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n54:     \"\"\"Handle errors by printing a message and optionally a traceback.\"\"\"\n55:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n56:     if verbose:\n57:         console.print_exception()\n58:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n59: \n60: \n61: @app.command()\n62: def pack(\n63:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n64:     agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\", help=\"Override the agent name.\"),\n65:     language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\", help=\"Programming language (python, java).\"),\n66:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\", help=\"Override the entrypoint command.\"),\n67:     port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\", help=\"Port to expose in the Dockerfile.\"),\n68:     build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\", help=\"Build strategy: local or cloud.\"),\n69:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description.\"),\n70:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for packaged workspace.\"),\n71:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n72: ) -> None:\n73:     \"\"\"Package an agent workspace for the AgentCube lifecycle.\"\"\"\n74:     with Progress(\n75:         SpinnerColumn(),\n76:         TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n77:         transient=True,\n78:     ) as progress:\n79:         task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n80:         try:\n81:             runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n82:             from pathlib import Path\n83:             workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n84:             result = runtime.pack(\n85:                 workspace_path,\n86:                 agent_name=agent_name,\n87:                 language=language,\n88:                 entrypoint=entrypoint,\n89:                 port=port,\n90:                 build_mode=build_mode,\n91:                 description=description,\n92:                 output=output,\n93:             )\n94:             progress.update(task, description=\"Done\")\n95:             console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent '[bold]{result['agent_name']}[/bold]' packaged successfully!\")\n96:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Workspace:[/dim] {result['workspace_path']}\")\n97:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Metadata: [/dim] {result['metadata_path']}\")\n98:         except Exception as e:\n99:             _handle_error(e, \"packaging agent\", verbose)\n100: \n101: \n102: @app.command()\n103: def build(\n104:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n105:     proxy: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"-p\", \"--proxy\", help=\"Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution.\"),\n106:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei).\"),\n107:     output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\", help=\"Output path for build artifacts.\"),\n108:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n109: ) -> None:\n110:     \"\"\"Build a container image from a packaged agent workspace.\"\"\"\n111:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n112:     try:\n113:         with Progress(\n114:             SpinnerColumn(),\n115:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n116:             transient=True,\n117:         ) as progress:\n118:             progress.add_task(\"Building agent...\", total=None)\n119:             runtime = BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n120:             result = runtime.build(\n121:                 workspace_path,\n122:                 proxy=proxy,\n123:                 cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n124:                 output=output,\n125:             )\n126: \n127:         metadata = runtime.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n128:         agent_name = metadata.agent_name if metadata else \"unknown\"\n129:         tag = metadata.version if metadata and metadata.version else \"latest\"\n130:         image_name = result.get(\"image_name\", agent_name)\n131:         image_size = result.get(\"image_size\", \"N/A\")\n132:         build_time = result.get(\"build_time\", \"N/A\")\n133: \n134:         console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent '[bold]{agent_name}[/bold]' built successfully!\")\n135:         console.print(f\"  [dim]Image:  [/dim] {image_name}:{tag}\")\n136:         console.print(f\"  [dim]Size:   [/dim] {image_size}\")\n137:         console.print(f\"  [dim]Time:   [/dim] {build_time}\")\n138:     except Exception as e:\n139:         _handle_error(e, \"building agent\", verbose)\n140: \n141: \n142: @app.command()\n143: def publish(\n144:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n145:     version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0).\"),\n146:     image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\", help=\"Image repository URL (required in local build mode).\"),\n147:     image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\", help=\"Username for image repository.\"),\n148:     image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\", help=\"Password for image repository.\"),\n149:     description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\", help=\"Agent description.\"),\n150:     region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\", help=\"Deployment region.\"),\n151:     cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\", help=\"Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei).\"),\n152:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: agentcube (AgentRuntime CR) or k8s (Deployment/Service).\"),\n153:     node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\", help=\"Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s deployment.\"),\n154:     replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\", help=\"Number of replicas for K8s deployment.\"),\n155:     namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\", help=\"The namespace for the deployment.\"),\n156:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n157: ) -> None:\n158:     \"\"\"Publish a packaged agent to a Kubernetes cluster.\"\"\"\n159:     workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n160: \n161:     if provider not in (\"agentcube\", \"k8s\"):\n162:         _handle_error(ValueError(f\"Unsupported provider: {provider}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'.\"), \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n163: \n164:     if node_port is not None and not (30000 <= node_port <= 32767):\n165:         _handle_error(ValueError(\"NodePort must be between 30000 and 32767\"), \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n166: \n167:     try:\n168:         with Progress(\n169:             SpinnerColumn(),\n170:             TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"),\n171:             transient=True,\n172:         ) as progress:\n173:             progress.add_task(\"Publishing agent...\", total=None)\n174:             runtime = PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)\n175:             result = runtime.publish(\n176:                 workspace_path,\n177:                 version=version,\n178:                 image_url=image_url,\n179:                 image_username=image_username,\n180:                 image_password=image_password,\n181:                 description=description,\n182:                 region=region,\n183:                 cloud_provider=cloud_provider,\n184:                 node_port=node_port,\n185:                 replicas=replicas,\n186:                 namespace=namespace,\n187:             )\n188: \n189:         from agentcube.services.metadata_service import MetadataService\n190:         _meta = MetadataService(verbose=verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n191:         agent_name = _meta.agent_name if _meta else \"unknown\"\n192: \n193:         if provider == \"agentcube\":\n194:             console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent '[bold]{agent_name}[/bold]' published successfully!\")\n195:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Workspace:[/dim] {workspace_path}\")\n196:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Agent ID: [/dim] {result.get('agent_id', 'N/A')}\")\n197:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Endpoint:[/dim] {result.get('agent_endpoint', 'N/A')}\")\n198:         else:\n199:             console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent '[bold]{agent_name}[/bold]' published successfully!\")\n200:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Workspace:[/dim] {workspace_path}\")\n201:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Deployment:[/dim] {result.get('deployment_name', 'N/A')}\")\n202:             console.print(f\"  [dim]Service: [/dim] {result.get('service_name', 'N/A')}\")\n203:             console.print(f\"  [dim]URL:     [/dim] {result.get('service_url', 'N/A')}\")\n204:     except Exception as e:\n205:         _handle_error(e, \"publishing agent\", verbose)\n\n(End of file - total 205 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"AgentCube CLI entry point.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport logging\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nimport typer\nfrom rich.console import Console\nfrom rich.progress import Progress, SpinnerColumn, TextColumn\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom ag