{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775856104708,"sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","part":{"id":"prt_d79439591001uHK0v55HBMeuRu","messageID":"msg_d794388580017G6msD6HLeV7sK","sessionID":"ses_286bec61bffehSsgEPkoMRhDU8","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_38f962d1f18b4741a269b99e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `invoke` command sends HTTP POST requests to a deployed agent endpoint and displays the response. The `status` command queries the deployment status of an agent from Kubernetes or workspace metadata and renders it as a Rich Table. Together they complete the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke/status`.\n\nBoth commands are **not yet implemented** — this design specifies the full technical implementation.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\n│   kubectl-agentcube invoke -f <ws> --payload '{}' [--header ...]     │\n│   kubectl-agentcube status -f <ws> [--provider agentcube|k8s]        │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │\n          ┌──────────────┴──────────────┐\n          ▼                             ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐       ┌─────────────────────┐\n│    InvokeRuntime    │       │    StatusRuntime    │\n│                     │       │                     │\n│ .invoke()           │       │ .get_status()       │\n│  ├─ _validate_      │       │  ├─ load metadata   │\n│  │   prerequisites  │       │  ├─ _get_cr_k8s_    │\n│  ├─ _invoke_agent_  │       │  │   status()        │\n│  │   via_agentcube  │       │  └─ _get_k8s_       │\n│  └─ _direct_http_   │       │     status()        │\n│     invocation()    │       │                     │\n└────────┬────────────┘       └────────┬────────────┘\n         │                             │\n         ▼                             ▼\n┌─────────────────────┐       ┌─────────────────────┐\n│  httpx / requests   │       │ AgentCubeProvider   │\n│  POST → endpoint    │       │ KubernetesProvider  │\n└─────────────────────┘       └────────┬────────────┘\n                                       │\n                                       ▼\n                              ┌─────────────────────┐\n                              │   Rich Table Output │\n                              │   Field | Value     │\n                              └─────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 2.2 Package Layout (invoke/status-relevant modules)\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                     — Dependencies, console script entry\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, exports (add InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime)\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n│   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, invoke(), status(), _handle_error\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports (add InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime)\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          — InvokeRuntime class (NEW)\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py          — StatusRuntime class (NEW)\n│   └── services/\n│       ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n│       ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n│       ├── docker_service.py           — DockerService\n│       ├── k8s_provider.py             — KubernetesProvider (add get_agent_status)\n│       └── agentcube_provider.py       — AgentCubeProvider (get_agent_runtime exists)\n└── tests/\n    ├── cli/\n    │   ├── test_invoke_command.py     — CLI invoke command tests (NEW)\n    │   └── test_status_command.py     — CLI status command tests (NEW)\n    └── runtime/\n        ├── test_invoke_runtime.py     — InvokeRuntime unit tests (NEW)\n        └── test_status_runtime.py     — StatusRuntime unit tests (NEW)\n```\n\n### 2.3 Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for agent_metadata.yaml |\n| `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client for invoke requests |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, colored output, tables |\n| `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s client library (optional, for status providers) |\n\nNo new dependencies are introduced — all are already declared in `pyproject.toml`.\n\n---\n\n## Component Design\n\n### 3.1 InvokeRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Any: ...\n    def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n        self, workspace_path: Path\n    ) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]: ...\n    async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n        self,\n        agent_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n        endpoint: str,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n    ) -> Any: ...\n    async def _direct_http_invocation(\n        self,\n        endpoint: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n        workspace_path: Path,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n#### 3.1.1 `invoke()` — Main orchestration\n\n```python\ndef invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any:\n    # 1. Validate prerequisites — returns (metadata, agent_id, endpoint)\n    metadata, agent_id, endpoint = self._validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)\n\n    # 2. Route by provider\n    if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n        return asyncio.run(\n            self._invoke_agent_via_agentcube(agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path)\n        )\n    else:\n        return asyncio.run(\n            self._direct_http_invocation(endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path)\n        )\n```\n\n#### 3.1.2 `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()`\n\nLoads metadata and validates that the agent has been published:\n\n```python\ndef _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]:\n    service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n    metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n    if not metadata.agent_id:\n        raise ValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n    if not metadata.agent_endpoint:\n        raise ValueError(\"Agent endpoint is not set in metadata. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n\n    return metadata, metadata.agent_id, metadata.agent_endpoint\n```\n\n#### 3.1.3 `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()` — AgentRuntime CR invocation\n\nKey behaviors:\n- **URL rewriting**: If `metadata.k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrite endpoint to:\n  ```\n  {base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n  ```\n  where `base` is extracted from the original endpoint, `namespace` and `agent_name` come from `metadata.k8s_deployment`.\n- **Session header**: If `metadata.session_id` exists, add `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header.\n- **HTTP POST**: Uses `httpx.AsyncClient` to POST JSON payload.\n\n**Known issue**: The existing implementation only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):` — if the condition is false, `return response` raises `UnboundLocalError`. This is out of scope for AR-023 but the CLI layer will catch it via `_handle_error`.\n\n```python\nasync def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id, payload, headers, endpoint, workspace_path):\n    metadata = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n    # URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR\n    if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n        namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n        agent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name)\n        # Extract base URL from original endpoint\n        base = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\").rsplit(\"/v1/\", 1)[0] if \"/v1/\" in endpoint else endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n        endpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n\n    # Build headers\n    request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n    if metadata.session_id:\n        request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n\n    # POST via httpx\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        response = await client.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=request_headers)\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n```\n\n#### 3.1.4 `_direct_http_invocation()` — Standard K8s invocation\n\nDirect HTTP POST to the agent endpoint (NodePort Service URL):\n\n```python\nasync def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint, payload, headers, workspace_path):\n    metadata = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose).load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n    request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n    if metadata.session_id:\n        request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        response = await client.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=request_headers)\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n```\n\n### 3.2 StatusRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def get_status(\n        self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n#### 3.2.1 `get_status()` — Main orchestration\n\n```python\ndef get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    provider = provider or self.provider\n    service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n    metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n    if not metadata.agent_id:\n        return {\"status\": \"not_published\"}\n\n    if provider == \"agentcube\":\n        return self._get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)\n    else:\n        return self._get_k8s_status(metadata)\n```\n\n#### 3.2.2 `_get_cr_k8s_status()` — AgentRuntime CR status\n\n```python\ndef _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\"\n    cr_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name) if metadata.k8s_deployment else metadata.agent_name\n\n    provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n    cr_object = provider.get_agent_runtime(cr_name)\n\n    if cr_object is None:\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\",\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n        }\n\n    cr_status = cr_object.get(\"status\", {})\n    if cr_status:\n        return {\n            \"status\": cr_status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\"),\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"endpoint\": cr_status.get(\"agentEndpoint\", metadata.agent_endpoint),\n            \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n            \"version\": metadata.version,\n        }\n    else:\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"created_no_status\",\n            \"agent_name\": metadata.agent_name,\n            \"cr_name\": cr_name,\n            \"namespace\": namespace,\n            \"version\": metadata.version,\n        }\n```\n\n#### 3.2.3 `_get_k8s_status()` — Standard K8s deployment status\n\nRequires `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` to be added (see §3.4):\n\n```python\ndef _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\") if metadata.k8s_deployment else \"default\"\n    deployment_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"deployment_name\", metadata.agent_name) if metadata.k8s_deployment else metadata.agent_name\n\n    provider = KubernetesProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n    return provider.get_agent_status(deployment_name)\n```\n\n### 3.3 CLI Commands (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n#### 3.3.1 `invoke` command\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef invoke(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n    payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\", help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent.\"),\n    header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\", help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service).\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Invoke a deployed agent with a JSON payload.\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Implementation flow:**\n1. Parse `payload` as JSON — on failure, print error in red and `typer.Exit(1)` (before `_handle_error`)\n2. Parse `header_list` — split each on first `:` to produce `Dict[str, str]`; on invalid format, print error and `typer.Exit(1)`\n3. Instantiate `InvokeRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n4. Call `runtime.invoke(Path(workspace), payload_dict, headers)`\n5. Print response (Rich-formatted JSON if dict, raw text otherwise)\n6. On exception, call `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)`\n\n#### 3.3.2 `status` command\n\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef status(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory.\", show_default=True),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\", help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service).\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", help=\"Enable detailed logging.\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Check the status of a deployed agent.\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Implementation flow:**\n1. Instantiate `StatusRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)`\n2. Call `runtime.get_status(Path(workspace), provider)`\n3. If `status == \"not_published\"`: print guidance to run `publish` first, `typer.Exit(1)`\n4. If `status == \"error\"`: print error details, `typer.Exit(1)`\n5. Render Rich `Table` with columns: Field, Value\n6. On exception (not `typer.Exit`), call `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)`\n\n### 3.4 KubernetesProvider extension\n\nAdd `get_agent_status()` method to `KubernetesProvider`:\n\n```python\ndef get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Get the status of a deployed agent.\n\n    Args:\n        agent_name: Name of the deployment.\n\n    Returns:\n        Dict with status, replicas, ready_replicas, available_replicas, etc.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        deployment = self._apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment_status(\n            name=agent_name,\n            namespace=self.namespace,\n        )\n        status = deployment.status\n        return {\n            \"status\": \"running\" if (status.ready_replicas and status.ready_replicas > 0) else \"pending\",\n            \"deployment_name\": agent_name,\n            \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            \"replicas\": status.replicas,\n            \"ready_replicas\": status.ready_replicas,\n            \"available_replicas\": status.available_replicas,\n            \"updated_replicas\": status.updated_replicas,\n        }\n    except ApiException as e:\n        if e.status == 404:\n            return {\n                \"status\": \"not_found\",\n                \"deployment_name\": agent_name,\n                \"namespace\": self.namespace,\n            }\n        raise\n```\n\n### 3.5 Sentinel Errors\n\n```python\n# InvokeRuntime\nValueError(\"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\nValueError(\"Agent endpoint is not set in metadata. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\")\n\n# StatusRuntime\n# Returns dict with status field — no exceptions for logical states\n\n# CLI layer\ntyper.Exit(1) — invalid JSON payload\ntyper.Exit(1) — invalid header format\ntyper.Exit(1) — not_published status\ntyper.Exit(1) — error status\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Flow Details\n\n### 4.1 invoke() CLI → Runtime → HTTP\n\n```\nCLI invoke()\n  │\n  ├── json.loads(payload) ──→ JSONDecodeError → print error, exit 1\n  │\n  ├── parse headers ──→ invalid format → print error, exit 1\n  │\n  ├── InvokeRuntime.invoke(workspace, payload_dict, headers)\n  │     │\n  │     ├── _validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n  │     │     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata()\n  │     │     ├── check metadata.agent_id → ValueError if missing\n  │     │     └── check metadata.agent_endpoint → ValueError if missing\n  │     │\n  │     └── provider == \"agentcube\"?\n  │           ├── YES → _invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n  │           │         ├── URL rewrite if k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"\n  │           │         ├── Add X-Agentcube-Session-Id if session_id exists\n  │           │         └── httpx.AsyncClient.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=headers)\n  │           │\n  │           └── NO → _direct_http_invocation()\n  │                     ├── Add X-Agentcube-Session-Id if session_id exists\n  │                     └── httpx.AsyncClient.post(endpoint, json=payload, headers=headers)\n  │\n  └── Print response (JSON-formatted or raw text)\n```\n\n### 4.2 status() CLI → Runtime → K8s API → Rich Table\n\n```\nCLI status()\n  │\n  ├── StatusRuntime.get_status(workspace, provider)\n  │     │\n  │     ├── MetadataService.load_metadata()\n  │     ├── check metadata.agent_id → return {\"status\": \"not_published\"} if missing\n  │     │\n  │     └── provider == \"agentcube\"?\n  │           ├── YES → _get_cr_k8s_status()\n  │           │         ├── AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime(cr_name)\n  │           │         ├── CR not found → {\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\", ...}\n  │           │         ├── CR has status → {\"status\": cr_status[\"status\"], \"endpoint\": ..., ...}\n  │           │         └── CR exists but no status → {\"status\": \"created_no_status\", ...}\n  │           │\n  │           └── NO → _get_k8s_status()\n  │                     ├── KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status(deployment_name)\n  │                     ├── Deployment not found → {\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}\n  │                     └── Deployment found → {\"status\": \"running\"/\"pending\", replicas, ...}\n  │\n  ├── status == \"not_published\"? → print guidance, exit 1\n  ├── status == \"error\"? → print error, exit 1\n  │\n  └── Render Rich Table:\n        ┌─────────────────┬──────────────────┐\n        │ Field           │ Value            │\n        ├─────────────────┼──────────────────┤\n        │ Agent Name      │ test-agent       │\n        │ Status          │ running          │\n        │ Endpoint        │ http://...       │\n        │ Version         │ v1.0.0           │\n        │ Provider        │ agentcube        │\n        │ ...             │ ...              │\n        └─────────────────┴──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 4.3 Header parsing logic\n\n```python\nheaders: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None\nif header_list:\n    headers = {}\n    for h in header_list:\n        if \":\" not in h:\n            typer.echo(f\"Error: Invalid header format '{h}'. Expected 'key:value'.\", err=True)\n            raise typer.Exit(1)\n        key, value = h.split(\":\", 1)\n        headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n```\n\n### 4.4 URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR\n\nWhen `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`:\n\n```python\nnamespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\nagent_name = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"cr_name\", metadata.agent_name)\nbase = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\").rsplit(\"/v1/\", 1)[0] if \"/v1/\" in endpoint else endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\nendpoint = f\"{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### 5.1 Error Handling Strategy\n\n| Error Type | Handling | Exit Code |\n|------------|----------|-----------|\n| Invalid JSON payload | Print error in red, exit immediately | 1 |\n| Invalid header format | Print error in red, exit immediately | 1 |\n| Agent not published (invoke) | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| Agent endpoint missing (invoke) | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| HTTP error during invoke | `_handle_error(e, \"invoking agent\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| K8s client init failure (status) | `_handle_error(e, \"getting status\", verbose)` | 1 |\n| not_published status | Print guidance, exit immediately | 1 |\n| error status | Print error details, exit immediately | 1 |\n| CR not found in K8s (status) | Display in table as status field | 0 |\n| Deployment not found (status) | Display in table as status field | 0 |\n\n### 5.2 CLI Error Handler (existing, reused)\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### 5.3 Verbose vs Global Verbose\n\nThe subcommand's local `--verbose` flag is passed to `_handle_error`, ensuring traceback is printed even if global `-v` was not passed on the root callback.\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n\n#### InvokeRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_ValidInvokeAgentCube` | Valid workspace, agentcube provider → invokes successfully |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_ValidInvokeK8s` | Valid workspace, k8s provider → direct HTTP invocation |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_NotPublished` | No agent_id in metadata → `ValueError` |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_MissingEndpoint` | No agent_endpoint in metadata → `ValueError` |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_URLRewriting` | k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\" → endpoint rewritten |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_SessionHeader` | session_id in metadata → X-Agentcube-Session-Id header added |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_CustomHeaders` | Custom headers passed through |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_HTTPError` | Non-2xx response → exception raised |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_UnboundLocalError` | Known bug: non-http endpoint → caught by CLI _handle_error |\n\n#### StatusRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestStatusRuntime_NotPublished` | No agent_id → `{\"status\": \"not_published\"}` |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_CRAgentCubeExists` | CR exists with status → correct status dict |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_CRAgentCubeNoStatus` | CR exists but no status field → `{\"status\": \"created_no_status\"}` |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_CRNotFound` | CR not found → `{\"status\": \"not_found_in_k8s\"}` |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentRunning` | K8s deployment ready → `{\"status\": \"running\", ...}` |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentPending` | K8s deployment not ready → `{\"status\": \"pending\", ...}` |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_K8sDeploymentNotFound` | K8s deployment 404 → `{\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}` |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_ProviderSelection` | Provider parameter routes to correct method |\n\n#### CLI invoke Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_invoke_command.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestInvokeCommand_SuccessAgentCube` | `invoke --provider agentcube` → success output, exit 0 |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_SuccessK8s` | `invoke --provider k8s` → success output, exit 0 |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_DefaultPayload` | `invoke` (no --payload) → uses `\"{}\"` |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_CustomPayload` | `invoke --payload '{\"key\":\"value\"}'` → correct JSON parsed |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_InvalidPayload` | `invoke --payload '{bad}'` → error, exit 1 |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_SingleHeader` | `invoke --header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"` → parsed |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_MultipleHeaders` | `invoke --header \"A:1\" --header \"B:2\"` → merged |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_InvalidHeader` | `invoke --header \"BadHeader\"` → error, exit 1 |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n| `TestInvokeCommand_HelpOutput` | `invoke --help` → shows all options |\n\n#### CLI status Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_status_command.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestStatusCommand_SuccessAgentCube` | `status --provider agentcube` → Rich Table, exit 0 |\n| `TestStatusCommand_SuccessK8s` | `status --provider k8s` → Rich Table, exit 0 |\n| `TestStatusCommand_NotPublished` | No agent_id → guidance message, exit 1 |\n| `TestStatusCommand_ErrorStatus` | status == \"error\" → error message, exit 1 |\n| `TestStatusCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n| `TestStatusCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n| `TestStatusCommand_HelpOutput` | `status --help` → shows all options |\n\n#### KubernetesProvider Tests (extension) (`tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusRunning` | Deployment ready → `{\"status\": \"running\", ...}` |\n| `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusPending` | Deployment not ready → `{\"status\": \"pending\", ...}` |\n| `TestK8sProvider_GetAgentStatusNotFound` | 404 → `{\"status\": \"not_found\", ...}` |\n\n### 6.2 Test Helpers\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workspace_with_published_metadata(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n    (ws / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n        \"agent_name: test-agent\\n\"\n        \"language: python\\n\"\n        \"entrypoint: python main.py\\n\"\n        \"port: 8080\\n\"\n        \"build_mode: local\\n\"\n        \"agent_id: test-agent-123\\n\"\n        \"agent_endpoint: http://router.example.com/v1/agents/test-agent\\n\"\n        \"k8s_deployment:\\n\"\n        \"  type: AgentRuntime\\n\"\n        \"  namespace: default\\n\"\n        \"  cr_name: test-agent\\n\"\n    )\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_httpx_client(mocker):\n    mock_response = MagicMock()\n    mock_response.json.return_value = {\"output\": \"hello world\"}\n    mock_response.raise_for_status.return_value = None\n\n    mock_client = MagicMock()\n    mock_client.__aenter__ = AsyncMock(return_value=mock_client)\n    mock_client.__aexit__ = AsyncMock(return_value=None)\n    mock_client.post.return_value = mock_response\n\n    mocker.patch(\"httpx.AsyncClient\", return_value=mock_client)\n    return mock_client\n```\n\n### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n\n- **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces\n- **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external deps)\n- **httpx.AsyncClient:** Mock `post()`, `__aenter__`, `__aexit__`\n- **AgentCubeProvider:** Mock `get_agent_runtime()`\n- **KubernetesProvider:** Mock `get_agent_status()`\n- **Console output:** Capture via `capfd` or `rich.console.Console(record=True)`\n\n### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `pytest tests/ -v` all pass\n2. `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` coverage ≥ 80%\n3. `ruff check agentcube/` no violations\n4. `mypy agentcube/` no type errors\n5. All InvokeRuntime and StatusRuntime public methods have unit tests\n6. Error paths tested (invalid payload, invalid header, not published, HTTP errors)\n7. Both provider flows tested (agentcube and k8s) for invoke and status\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n1. **async/await in CLI**: `InvokeRuntime` uses `async` methods internally but the CLI command runs them synchronously via `asyncio.run()`. This avoids making the Typer command async.\n\n2. **httpx vs requests**: The invoke command uses `httpx` (already a dependency) for async HTTP. The Python SDK uses `requests`, but the CLI layer should use `httpx` for consistency with the async pattern in `InvokeRuntime`.\n\n3. **URL rewriting edge case**: If the original endpoint doesn't contain `/v1/`, the base URL extraction falls back to the full endpoint (stripped of trailing slashes). This handles both `http://router/v1/...` and `http://localhost:30080` formats.\n\n4. **Session header spelling**: The header is `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (note: not `X-AgentCube-Session-Id`). This matches the SDK's `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"` (lowercase, HTTP headers are case-insensitive).\n\n5. **Provider default**: Both commands default to `provider=\"agentcube\"`, consistent with the `publish` command.\n\n6. **KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()**: This method does not exist yet and must be added. It queries `read_namespaced_deployment_status()` and returns a dict with status fields. 404 is handled gracefully (returns `not_found` status dict, not an exception).\n\n7. **Known UnboundLocalError**: `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube` has a known bug where `response` is only assigned inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`. If the endpoint doesn't start with `http`, `return response` raises `UnboundLocalError`. This is out of scope for AR-023 — the CLI layer catches it via `_handle_error` and the user sees a friendly error message.\n\n8. **Rich Table rendering**: The status command renders a table with all key-value pairs from the status dict. The table should include at minimum: Agent Name, Status, Endpoint, Version, Provider.\n\n9. **No new dependencies**: All required libraries (httpx, rich, typer, pydantic, pyyaml, kubernetes) are already declared in `pyproject.toml`.\n\n10. **runtime/__init__.py update**: After creating `invoke_runtime.py` and `status_runtime.py`, update `runtime/__init__.py` to export `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime`.\n\n11. **agentcube/__init__.py update**: After creating the runtime classes, update the top-level `__init__.py` to include `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` in exports (note: `StatusRuntime` was explicitly not exported before — this AR adds it).\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-023/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\">\nERROR [28:35] \"CustomObjectsApi\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [125:20] Type \"str | list[list[Unknown] | dict[Unknown, list[Unknown] | dict[Unknown, Unknown] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None] | dict[Unknown, list[list[Unknown] | dict[Unknown, Unknown] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None] | dict[Unknown, Unknown] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None] | Unknown | _Date | datetime | tuple[str | list[list[Unknown] | dict[Unknown, list[Unknown] | dict[Unknown, Unknown] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None] | dict[Unknown, list[list[Unknown] | dict[Unknown, Unknown] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None] | dict[Unknown, Unknown]